<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-07T10:29:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-07T10:29:00-05:00" n="254" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1977</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Francis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Petrograd</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-07T20:00:00+04:31"><hi rend="italic">June 7,
                                            1918, 8 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 9, 2.45
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>9. Papers state <persName corresp="#p_CGV1">Chicherin</persName>
                                answered consuls<note n="2" xml:id="d254fn2">See the Ambassador’s
                                    telegram No. 241, June 3, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_188">p. 188</ref>.</note> by saying no objection
                                to departure Czechs if disarmed. Have telegraphed to Vologda
                                advising reply be delayed until instructions received from our
                                governments. <persName corresp="#p_PDC1">Poole</persName> advises
                                that Soviet order to disarm was dictated by Germans and many German
                                and Austrian prisoners fighting with Red Guard against Slovaks; that
                                Soviet government spreading Bolshevik doctrine among Slovaks and
                                endeavoring every way to interfere with departure claiming that
                                Slovak organization is counter-revolution movement.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_FDR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>